ex edicto praetoris. On entering office, the praetor issued a statement of the legal principles on which he pro- posed to base his administration. In the main, each praetor , adopted, with modificatione and additions, the edict of his predecessor3 and thus the edictum perpetuum, or tralaticium came to be a standing body of civil law.
